derivation.yuyuan_name: Middle English: from Old French degnier, from Latin dignare, dignari 'deem worthy', from dignus 'worthy'

entry.def: If you say that someone deigned to do something, you are expressing your disapproval of the fact that they did it unwillingly, because they thought they were too important to do it.

example.ex: At last, Harper deigned to speak...

means.word_mean: 1. do something that one considers to be below one's dignity
